cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image-based plant phenotyping and proposes a method for generating synthetic plant images using a deep convolutional network. The use of generative neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of state-of-the-art machine learning approaches and regression-based models, which further supports its potential categorization under cs.LG and cs.AI. The mention of leaf segmentation and counting suggests that it could also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of adversarial networks for generating synthetic images suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
